(50, '<div class="post-image" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px -1px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 17px; vertical-align: baseline; position: relative; background: transparent;"><img alt="forgemaster-full" class="attachment-single wp-post-image" src="http://1.hiexistence.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/forgemaster-full-1000x450.jpg" style="background:transparent; border:none; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:auto; margin:0px; max-width:100%; outline:0px; padding:0px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; width:705px" /><small>Image by&nbsp;<a href="http://www.artofbrandonmoore.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/forgemaster-full.jpg" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: white; outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;" target="_blank">Brandon Moore</a></small></div>\n\n<div class="post-content jpibfi_container" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 40px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 17px; vertical-align: baseline; overflow: hidden; background: transparent;">\n<blockquote>\n<p>&ldquo;Sub-doses of 10 to 20 micrograms&nbsp;<em>(of LSD)</em>&nbsp;allow me to increase my focus, open my heart, and achieve breakthrough results while remaining integrated within my routine. My wit, response time, and visual and mental acuity seem greater than normal on it.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p style="text-align:right">- Madeline,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.amazon.com/The-Psychedelic-Explorers-Guide-Therapeutic/dp/1594774021/&amp;tag=highexis-20" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">The Psychedelic Explorer&rsquo;s Guide</a></p>\n<a class="tweetThis" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.highexistence.com%2Fmicro-dose-lsd-psychedelic%2F&amp;text=%E2%80%9CSub-doses%20of%2010%20to%2020%20micrograms%20(of%20LSD)%C2%A0allow%20me%20to%20increase%20my%20focus,%20open%20my%20heart,%20and%20achieve..." style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 13px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(24, 159, 211); text-decoration: none; position: absolute; left: 0px; top: 75px; text-align: center; width: 53px; line-height: 25px; border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px; border: 1px solid rgb(226, 226, 226) !important; outline: 0px !important; -webkit-box-shadow: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2) 0px 1px 0px inset, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588) 0px 1px 2px !important; box-shadow: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2) 0px 1px 0px inset, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588) 0px 1px 2px !important; background-image: -webkit-linear-gradient(top, rgb(255, 255, 255), rgb(248, 248, 248)) !important; background-attachment: initial; background-color: rgb(76, 182, 233); background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: initial; background-repeat: repeat-x !important;" target="_blank" title="Tweet this quote">Tweet</a></blockquote>\n\n<p>On a beautiful morning in Amsterdam I grabbed my vial of LSD, diluted down with half high grade vodka and half distilled water, and told my friend to trust me and open his mouth. While semi-carefully measuring the droplets for his dose, I told him to whirl it around in his mouth for a few minutes before swallowing the neuro-chemical concoction. After I vaccinated him against the pre-occupations and worries of the modern anxiety-ridden subject (LSD is a well known anxiolytic), I quickly followed suit.</p>\n\n<p><strong>We had one of the best walking conversation of&nbsp;our lives.</strong></p>\n\n<p>I first became immensely&nbsp;curious about the potential of micro-dosing psychedelics after reading&nbsp;<a href="http://www.themorningnews.org/article/the-heretic" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">this captivating story</a>&nbsp;about James Fadiman and his research. After a few test-runs, I knew I stumbled upon something significant.</p>\n\n<p>Today we are&nbsp;witnessing the birth of a truly remarkable epoch. With the psychedelic renaissance well under way, consisting of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.scpr.org/news/2014/05/19/44178/psychedelic-science-the-surge-in-psychiatric-resea/?utm_content=buffer6fe92&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_source=facebook.com&amp;utm_campaign=buffer" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">new fascinating research</a>, the coming out of thousands of&nbsp;<a href="http://reset.me/story/howpsychedelicssavedmylife/" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">individuals</a>&nbsp;and the introduction of many, hitherto unknown, psychoactive plants steeped in their cultural context of healing and initiation, we are now facing some new and interesting questions.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>What types of consciousness are possible, and how are we to navigate these?</li>\n	<li>Which plants and substances are beneficial in which situations?</li>\n	<li>How are we to make sense of these shamanic wisdom traditions, as our own euro-shamanistic traditions and the&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eleusinian_Mysteries#Entheogenic_theories" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">Eleusinian mysteries</a>&nbsp;seem to be lost in time forever?</li>\n	<li>And how can we develop new ways of healing, new rituals embedded in cultural meaning that are able cure our current &ldquo;<a href="http://reset.me/video/how-psychedelics-can-cure-our-collective-insanity/" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">collective insanity</a>&ldquo;?</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>I think one of the more fruitful directions we can take is towards is micro-dosing. Micro-dosing is taking sub-perceptual (6-25 microgram LSD,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.stephengrayvision.com/2009/11/01/the-benefits-of-low-dose-psilocybin-mushrooms/" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">0.2-0.5 gram dried mushrooms</a>,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.drugs-forum.com/forum/showthread.php?t=78537" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">50-75 microgram mescaline HCL</a>) while keeping up with ones daily activities,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.maps.org/news-letters/v21n1/v21n1-25to29.pdf" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">engaging in extreme sports</a>, appreciating nature or enhancing one&rsquo;s spiritual practice. This manner of integrating psychedelics, also known as a<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychedelic_therapy#Psycholytic_therapy" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">psycholytic dose</a>, doesn&rsquo;t inhibit ego-functioning as the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Nrj1X6TzEXo" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">&lsquo;heroic&rsquo; Terence McKenna</a>&nbsp;dose does. It can be much easier integrated into everyday functioning. It is known&nbsp;that Albert Hofmann, the first synthesizer of LSD, continued this practice well into his old age while&nbsp;<a href="http://www.amazon.com/The-Psychedelic-Explorers-Guide-Therapeutic/dp/1594774021/&amp;tag=highexis-20" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">saying</a>&nbsp;&ldquo;it would have gone on to be used as Ritalin if it hadn&rsquo;t been so harshly scheduled.&rdquo;</p>\n\n<h2>What are the effects of micro-dosing that makes it so interesting?</h2>\n\n<p>James Oroc, the author of the amazing book&nbsp;<a href="http://www.amazon.com/Tryptamine-Palace-5-MeO-DMT-Sonoran-Desert/dp/1594772991/&amp;tag=highexis-20" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">Tryptamine Palace: 5-MeO-DMT and the Sonoran Desert Toad</a>, while writing about&nbsp;<a href="http://www.maps.org/news-letters/v21n1/v21n1-25to29.pdf" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">the secret affair</a>&nbsp;between psychedelics and extreme sports, stated that while taking psychedelics at lower doses, the &ldquo;cognitive functioning, emotional balance, and physical stamina were actually found to be improved.&rdquo; For some, this might not come as a surprise, since Hofmann already spoke in a&nbsp;<a href="https://www.erowid.org/culture/characters/hofmann_albert/hofmann_albert_interview1.shtml" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">now famous interview</a>&nbsp;that &ldquo;Lysergic acid diethyl amide (LSD) is related in chemical structure to nicotinic acid diethylamide, known to be an effective&nbsp;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analeptic" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;" target="_blank">analeptic</a>.&rdquo; But there&rsquo;s more, as James Oroc&nbsp;<a href="http://www.maps.org/news-letters/v21n1/v21n1-25to29.pdf" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(42, 126, 186); outline: 0px !important; background: transparent;">eloquently put</a>,</p>\n\n<blockquote>&nbsp;</blockquote>\n</div>\n'),
