 issues on your own as they arise.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class="bs-callout bs-callout-warning" style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 20px; margin: -5px 0px 20px; border-width: 1px 1px 1px 5px; border-style: solid; border-color: rgb(238, 238, 238) rgb(238, 238, 238) rgb(238, 238, 238) rgb(240, 173, 78); border-top-left-radius: 3px; border-top-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-right-radius: 3px; border-bottom-left-radius: 3px;">\n<h4>Deprecated&nbsp;<code>.pull-right</code>&nbsp;alignment</h4>\n\n<p>As of v3.1.0, we&#39;ve deprecated&nbsp;<code>.pull-right</code>&nbsp;on dropdown menus. To right-align a menu, use&nbsp;<code>.dropdown-menu-right</code>. Right-aligned nav components in the navbar use a mixin version of this class to automatically align the menu. To override it, use&nbsp;<code>.dropdown-menu-left</code>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class="zero-clipboard" style="box-sizing: border-box; position: relative;"><span style="color:rgb(119, 119, 119); font-size:12px">Copy</span></div>\n\n<div class="highlight" style="box-sizing: border-box; padding: 9px 14px; margin-bottom: 14px; border: 1px solid rgb(225, 225, 232); border-top-left-radius: 4px; border-top-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-right-radius: 4px; border-bottom-left-radius: 4px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 249);">\n<pre>\n<code><span style="color:rgb(47, 111, 159)"> <span style="color:rgb(79, 159, 207)">class=</span><span style="color:rgb(212, 73, 80)">&quot;dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right&quot;</span> <span style="color:rgb(79, 159, 207)">role=</span><span style="color:rgb(212, 73, 80)">&quot;menu&quot;</span> <span style="color:rgb(79, 159, 207)">aria-labelledby=</span><span style="color:rgb(212, 73, 80)">&quot;dLabel&quot;</span><span style="color:rgb(47, 111, 159)">&gt;</span>\n  ...\n</span></code></pre>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Headers</h3>\n\n<p>Add a header to label sections of actions in any dropdown menu.</p>\n\n<div class="zero-clipboard" style="box-sizing: border-box; position: relative;"><span style="c